\f0\b \cf0 Money, time, and energy as resources
\f1\b0 \
Cash is king, but rare for rebels. Time slips fastest\'97bills, jobs, life. Energy? The hardest: burnout lurks after endless meetings. Track them ruthlessly: log hours spent, dollars pooled, rest taken. No resource is free; all demand audit.\

\f0\b Creativity over money
\f1\b0 \
Big budgets buy ads; ingenuity wins wars. No cash for protests? Guerrilla theater: flash mobs in corporate lobbies, chalk art on sidewalks, viral memes mocking CEOs. Free tools abound\'97open-source software, public parks, word-of-mouth. Hack the system: turn their waste into your gain (dumpster-dived supplies), their events into your teach-ins. David slays Goliath with slings, not swords.\

\f0\b Finding allies and resource sharing
\f1\b0 \
Solo scarcity kills; collective abundance empowers. Barter skills: your legal know-how for their graphic design. Form co-ops\'97shared office space, bulk buys, rotating childcare. Mutual aid networks pool funds: one\'92s GoFundMe seeds another\'92s bail. Allies aren\'92t just bodies; they\'92re multipliers. Seek bartering partners in your mapped community\'97unions for muscle, churches for venues, hackers for data.\

\f0\b Long-term resource management
\f1\b0 \
Sprints thrill; marathons conquer. Pace yourself: delegate tasks, automate routines (scripts for outreach), recharge with breaks. Build reserves\'97emergency funds, skill libraries, backup plans. Sustainability means renewal: victories fund more, lessons cut waste. Track ROI: Did that rally convert skeptics? Adjust.\
Resource reality isn\'92t limitation; it\'92s liberation from dependency. The powerful hoard; you adapt. With smart husbandry, your scraps become their nightmare.\
Book 3 begins: The Arsenal. Tactics to wield, illusions to shatter. Power isn\'92t held\'97it's seized.\
Conserve wisely, strike boldly.\
